# Changelog
All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0
.html).


## [Zwischenabgabe 1] - 2019-12-22
### Added
- User can choose to play hotseat, singleplayer or to go to the lobby from the 
  start screen.
- Game view displays the board and all relevant buttons and notifications
  to play the game.

##[Zwischenabgabe 2] - 2020-01-12
### Added
- Shell to play reversi in hotseat and singleplayer mode within the console
- model that consists of necessary logic, so that reversi could be played in hotseat mode or in singleplayer mode
- Implemented full functionality to play a hotseat and a singleplayer game with
  the GUI.
- When the game has finished a message is shown to the user, with the 
  information who has won.
- Label that shows the current player.
- User can quit the game with the GUI.
- User can reset a game with the GUI.
- Possible moves can be shown to the user by the click of a button.
- Possible moves that are currently shown can be deleted from the board by the 
  click of a button.

### Changed
- In the game lobby the button "quit" has changed to "back" and does not ask 
  anymore to quit the lobby.
- Bigger size of the window for a better user experience.
